cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about a novel algorithm for visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves mathematical derivations and efficient model training, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on benchmark datasets, indicating that it may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
